Unlocks:
The player can now craft and wear Witchwood Howl Collectors.


Agility Shortcut: Mos Le’Harmless — Small island north-east of Mos Le’Harmless. (Requires Agility level 61.)


The player can now recruit Brother Thaddeus as a crewmate, found on Entrana.


Brother Thaddeus enhances boats’ defences and heals small amounts of hull damage with his prayers.


Otherwise his crew stats are minor (H1 P1 D1).


New Sea Slayer Master: Thalos the Deep — gives on-boat Slayer tasks.


Access to a new Mercenary ship salvaging area: The Ship Graveyard.


Ability to fight Sea Horrors north of Mos Le’Harmless.


Access to the Cave Terror boss fight.


Can only be fought when the player is on a Cave Horrors Slayer task.


Requires a fully charged Howl Collector or Howling Vocal Cords Slayer Helmet attachment.


After the quest, the Cave Terror has a more limited movement area since it is now chained.


During the fight, if a player goes out of melee range, it starts using the Rock Hurl attack at accelerating speed, ignoring player prayers until the player returns within reach.


Burrowing Lunge attack now moves in a circular motion.



Cave Terror Unique Drops:
Black Mask — 1/100


New Item: Howling Vocal Cords — 1/1000
When attached to a Slayer Helmet, permanently grants resistance to Cave Horror and Cave Terror howls.


New Item: Blackstone Claws — 1/500
Has identical stats and requirements to Burning Claws.


Special Attack — “Beastily Lunge”


Energy Cost: 50%


The player lunges at their opponent, attacking with increased accuracy and power, piercing them with the claws and causing them to bleed.


Bleed inflicted by Blackstone Claws causes the player to lose 9 Hitpoints over 9 seconds (15 ticks).


The player can attack their opponent from 5 squares away, leaping at the target and then landing in the square next to the opponent.


If the player is frozen or stunned, they cannot use the special attack.



